ZH: 我们必须为我们的行为做出申辩。
EN: We must provide a defense for our actions.

ZH: 这是一个非常严肃的问题，我想要为自己的言论进行申辩。
EN: This is a very serious matter, and I would like to offer a defense for my statement.

ZH: 在法庭上，你将有机会申辩。
EN: In a court of law, you will have the chance to make your defense.

ZH: 我们必须准备好一切来申辩。
EN: We must be prepared with everything to make our defense.

ZH: 他花了很多时间来准备他的申辩。
EN: He spent a lot of time preparing his defense.

ZH: 我们本可以通过合理的申辩来解决这个问题。
EN: We could have resolved this issue through reasonable defense.

ZH: 他们的申辩没有通过。
EN: Their defense did not succeed.

ZH: 请你先听完我的申辩再作出判断。
EN: Please listen to my defense before making a judgment.

ZH: 他在法庭上为自己申辩，但并没有成功。
EN: He defended himself in court, but he didn't succeed.

ZH: 我必须申辩，因为这涉及我的名誉。
EN: I have to defend myself because it involves my reputation.

ZH: 律师向法庭提出了一份申辩陈述。
EN: The lawyer presented a defense statement to the court.

ZH: 申辩是每个人的权利。
EN: Defense is the right of every person.

ZH: 他们提出了多种申辩理由来证明他们的清白。
EN: They presented multiple defense arguments to prove their innocence.

ZH: 她发表了一篇长篇申辩声明，解释了她的行为。
EN: She released a lengthy defense statement explaining her actions.

ZH: 他们的申辩被接受了，并且被判定无罪。
EN: Their defense was accepted, and they were found not guilty.

ZH: 在面临指控时，他们必须提供充分的申辩材料。
EN: When faced with charges, they must provide sufficient defense evidence.

ZH: 申辩需要有充分的证据支持。
EN: Defense needs to be supported by sufficient evidence.

ZH: 在课堂上，学生可以提供申辩来解释他们的行为。
EN: In the classroom, students can provide a defense to explain their actions.

ZH: 只有通过申辩，他们才能证明自己是无辜的。
EN: Only through defense can they prove their innocence.

ZH: 他们花费了大量时间准备他们的申辩辩词。
EN: They spent a lot of time preparing their defense arguments.

ZH: 他们为自己的错误做出了申辩。
EN: They made a defense for their mistakes.
